      "content": "It is crucial to be transparent while carefully managing the narrative around the exposed data. Instead of labeling it a \"breach,\" you could frame the situation as a \"security configuration error\" or an \"unintended exposure.\" Emphasize that the issue was resolved immediately upon detection and that the only affected data was limited to a small subset of non-sensitive emails. This controls the story by focusing on swift remediation rather than the initial failure.",
